## Requirements

- **macOS** — AppleScript automation requires macOS
- **Node.js** >= 18 — For the MCP server
- **Python** >= 3.10 — For the chat export preprocessor
- **DingTalk Desktop** — Must be installed and logged in

## macOS Permissions (Important)

This skill controls DingTalk desktop via AppleScript. macOS requires granting Codex **Full Disk Access** and **Accessibility** permissions. Without these, the skill cannot read DingTalk window content.

### 1. Accessibility

Allows Codex to control other apps (DingTalk) via AppleScript:

```
System Settings > Privacy & Security > Accessibility
```

Click the `+` button and add:
- **Codex** (ChatGPT Codex desktop app)
- **Terminal** (if running via terminal)

### 2. Full Disk Access

Allows Codex to read application windows and UI elements:

```
System Settings > Privacy & Security > Full Disk Access
```

Click the `+` button and add **Codex**.

### 3. Automation Permission

On first run, macOS will prompt: "Allow Codex to control DingTalk?" — click **Allow**.

To manage manually:

```
System Settings > Privacy & Security > Automation
```

Confirm **DingTalk** is checked under Codex.

> ⚠️ You must restart Codex after granting permissions for changes to take effect.

